TY  - JOUR
T1  - Dynamically Integrating Knowledge in Teams: Transforming Resources into Performance
AU  - Gardner, Heidi K.
AU  - Gino, Francesca
AU  - Staats, Bradley R.
Y1  - 2012/04/30
PY  - 2012
DA  - 2012/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2010.0604
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2010.0604
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 998
EP  - 1022
VL  - 55
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In knowledge-based environments, teams must develop a systematic approach to integrating knowledge resources throughout the course of projects in order to perform effectively. Yet many teams fail to do so. Drawing on the resource-based view of the firm, we examine how teams can develop a knowledge-integration capability to dynamically integrate members' resources into higher performance. We distinguish among three sets of resources?relational, experiential, and structural?and propose that they differentially influence a team's knowledge integration capability. We test our theoretical framework using data on knowledge workers in professional services and discuss implications for research and practice.
